      <h1 class='title'>Finance Bill</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 26 March 2003 vol 402 c16WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_16ws' title='Col. 16WS &mdash; HC Deb 26 March 2003 vol 402 c16WS' name='column_16ws' href='#column_16ws' rel='bookmark'>16WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0402P0-04863'>
        <a name='S6CV0402P0_20030326_CWS_6'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-dawn-primarolo' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0402P0_20030326_CWS_6' title='Link to this speech by Ms Dawn Primarolo' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-dawn-primarolo" title="Ms Dawn Primarolo">The Paymaster General (Dawn Primarolo)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0402P0-04863">Legislation will be introduced in the <a href="/bills/finance-bill">Finance Bill</a> 2003 which will counter tax avoidance used by individuals attempting to exploit the 100 per cent. rate of capital allowances available for expenditure on information and communications technology. The legislation will prevent first year allowances being available to anyone who exploits software or software rights by the granting of rights to use or otherwise deal with that computer software. The measure will apply to expenditure incurred on or after today.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
